{
  "stem": "15197.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, of course.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The papers, I got through illegal ways.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first paper I got to a friend which worked together with our people-- with this small group of underground people on the Polish side.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was Anna Wonchalska-- her name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was a socialist but she-- Michael Klepfisz, who was the one who introduced me to her, brought me over to her house.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And little by little, she likes me and she told me, you know-- Vladka-- what?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You need papers to have an original Kin Card-- the identification paper from-- by-- made officially by the German administration.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had a little daughter, she told me, who was two years old.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She died.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I will take the birth certificate out from this small town from my daughter and you will become my daughter.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I became her daughter-- Anna Wonchalska's daughter.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was my first identification card.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The real identification card, which I didn't have for too long.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because always, somebody was blackmailing and it was always a danger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you have too long and somebody else got arrested, you are afraid that the person can give you out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But Anna Wonchalska was really one of the righteous Polish women.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she was like a mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And once, on the-- during the Uprising, when I was on the Polish side, I need some help.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And always when I need help, I turned to Anna Wonchalska.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She had contact with Polish people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she was helping us-- the Jewish-- the few Jewish underground workers on the Polish side, which belonged to the fighters' organization.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When Kashak Rotheiser and Zalman Friedrich came out from the ghetto looking for help to save a few ghetto fighters, we turned, as usually, to Anna Wonchalska for some contacts.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
